correctness.rationale: Major parts of the extraction are untraceable or inconsistent with the article and there are schema–semantic issues. Key problems: (1) Multiple ALD processes are described (γ‑Al2O3 SCL at 150 °C then PDA, ZnO SCL at 250 °C, and In2‑xGaxO3 at 250 °C), but only a single process (In2‑xGaxO3) is provided; the ZnO (and Al2O3) ALD processes are missing. (2) Substrate is set to “Si (100)”, whereas the IGO film is deposited on a ZnO(002)/γ‑Al2O3(222)/Si stack; this is incomplete. (3) Supercycle design is incorrect: the paper specifies In:Ga sub‑cycle ratios (In‑only, 6/1, 4/1, 2/1) with an In2O3/Ga2O3 sequence; the JSON gives only a generic count=1 and omits the actual ratios. (4) Composition/device mismatch: chemicalComposition is In1.4Ga0.6O3, but device metrics (μ_FE=95.5 cm2/V·s, V_TH=1.33 V, SS=166 mV/dec, I_ON/I_OFF≈1e8) correspond to Ga‑free ho In2O3/ZnO. (5) Many parameters are fabricated and not traceable: reactor name, pressure (10 mTorr), GPC (0.2 Å), cycle count (250), saturation/nucleation period, dosing/purge times (100 ms), and flow rates (50/100 sccm) are not reported. (6) Optical and film electrical properties (n, absorption, bandgap, resistivity, carrier density, and “Hall measurements”) are not given in the article; mobility cited is device μ_FE, not Hall. (7) Film density (5.5 g/dm3) and uniformity/conformality values are unreported; the density value/unit is also not physically plausible. (8) Carrier/purging gases are asserted as Ar without explicit support. Correct items include PEALD method, O2 plasma co‑reactant, 100 W RF power, 250 °C deposition temperature, ho crystallinity, roughness (~0.34 nm), and 5 nm channel thickness. To fix: add separate processes for ZnO and γ‑Al2O3 SCLs; correct the substrate to the actual stack; provide the correct supercycle ratios; align device metrics with the selected composition (or choose the composition matching the device); and remove or mark unknown all unreported parameters (pressure, GPC, times, flows, optical/electrical film properties, density, uniformity/conformality, gases) and correct the characterization method.

completeness.rationale: Largely incomplete and not traceable. (1) Missing processes: The article reports three distinct PEALD processes that should be represented as separate processes—Al2O3 SCL (TMA + O2 plasma, 150 °C, RF 50 W, O2/[Ar+O2]=10%), ZnO SCL (DEZ + O2 plasma, 250 °C, RF 100 W, O2=50% of [Ar+O2]), and In2−xGaxO3 channels (DATI + TMG + O2 plasma, 250 °C, RF 100 W), with both ho (on ZnO/θ‑Al2O3) and rp (direct on θ‑Al2O3) variants. Only one process is provided. (2) Target mismatch: The task focuses on ZnO ALD, but the extracted process is In2−xGaxO3; no ZnO deposition process is included. (3) Supercycle design not captured: The In/Ga subcycle ratios that control composition (In-only, 6/1, 4/1, 2/1) are not represented; the provided supercycleDesign is incorrect/incomplete. (4) Many parameters are fabricated or not reported in the article, violating traceability: chamber pressure (10 mTorr), GPC (0.2 Å/cycle), number of cycles (250), dosing/purge times (100 ms), flow rates (50 sccm), nucleation period (5 cycles), saturation state, uniformity (2%), conformality (AR 10), and film density (5.5 g/dm3). (5) Reactant selection ambiguities: Carrier/purging gas set to Ar are not stated; the article gives only plasma gas composition fractions. (6) Composition-performance inconsistency: chemicalComposition is In1.4Ga0.6O3 but device metrics correspond to ho In2O3 (μFE 95.5 cm2/Vs, VTH 1.33 V). If the composition is In1.4Ga0.6O3, μFE≈71.0 cm2/Vs and VTH≈1.70 V should be used. (7) Film electrical properties misattributed: mobility under materialProperties is labeled as Hall measurements (not reported) and duplicates device μFE; resistivity and carrier density are not provided in the paper. (8) Schema alignment issues: aldMethod should list PEALD for Al2O3, ZnO, and In/Ga oxides; supercycle counts should be provided per subcycle (In2O3 and Ga2O3). To improve, add separate processes for Al2O3 SCL, ZnO SCL, ho In2−xGaxO3, and rp In2−xGaxO3; correct precursor/gas details; align device metrics with composition; and remove or justify any parameters not reported by the authors.
